{
  "stem": "9730.1",
  "chunk_idx": 3,
  "model": "openai/gpt-oss-120b",
  "elapsed_s": 8.2,
  "sentences_input": [
    {
      "segment_idx": 21,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 6,
      "text": "For instance, it was customary that in the prayer books that we used, people had made notations, that, for instance, [PAUSES FOR 3 SECONDS] on this day in the year [PAUSES FOR 3 SECONDS] 1884, it snowed on Passover in April.",
      "word_count": 41
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 21,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 7,
      "text": "And-- and so, we were-- this always brought back reminiscences of former times.",
      "word_count": 13
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 22,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "Well, [PAUSES FOR 3 SECONDS] I remember one holiday, which in this case, this doesn't apply so much to the home, but rather to the synagogue we had.",
      "word_count": 28
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 22,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "[NON-ENGLISH] was being celebrated in the synagogue by bringing in-- actually bringing in young trees from the surrounding woods, putting them in clay pots along the aisles and the pews.",
      "word_count": 30
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 22,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 2,
      "text": "And so there was always sort of a-- a forest inside the synagogue.",
      "word_count": 13
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 22,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 3,
      "text": "That's one thing that stands out.",
      "word_count": 6
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 23,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "We ourselves did not, but our neighbors did.",
      "word_count": 8
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 23,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "And we availed ourselves of-- of that sukkah.",
      "word_count": 8
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 24,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "Yes, I did.",
      "word_count": 3
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 24,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "And that, of course, was a big event for-- for me.",
      "word_count": 11
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 24,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 2,
      "text": "I-- I studied many months before then for that.",
      "word_count": 9
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 24,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 3,
      "text": "And it also meant that the reciter, who was the head of the Jewish congregation, by name of Hahn, made the most of it, because he saw his charges dwindle to almost none.",
      "word_count": 33
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 24,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 4,
      "text": "And after me, there were perhaps two more boys who became bar mitzvah in-- in Walldorf.",
      "word_count": 16
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 24,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 5,
      "text": "So he made the most of it, and he really tried to instill in me all the things that were in his command.",
      "word_count": 23
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 24,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 6,
      "text": "He, by the way, had a son who became a rabbi of renown in-- in the town-- in the city of Mainz.",
      "word_count": 22
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 24,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 7,
      "text": "And later on, he had a pulpit in New York City.",
      "word_count": 11
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 25,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "His name was Hugo Hahn.",
      "word_count": 5
    }
  ],
